recipe.label: Vegetarian Banana Leaf Tamales
ingredientLines: 1 pound package of banana leaves, frozen or fresh (available at most Asian or Mexican markets)

2 pounds of already prepared tamale masa, or 3 cups masa harina (masa flour NOT regular corn meal) Note that prepared masa often has lard in it, so if you are going vegetarian on this recipe consider making your own masa from scratch, or buying a vegetarian prepared masa.
3 large cloves garlic, peeled and chopped
2 calabacitas (Mexican summer squash, can substitute zucchini), roughly chopped (1 1/2 cups)
2 plum tomatoes, cored and chopped (about 1 cup)
1 small bunch of spinach (about 15-20 leaves), rinsed, stems removed and discarded, chopped
12 ounces Monterey Jack cheese, cut into 3" x 3/4" x 1/2" pieces
A large stockpot with a steamer rack

recipe.label: Vegetarian Matzo Ball Soup
ingredientLines: 2 cups matzo meal (I prefer to buy unsalted crackers and pulse in the food processor)
1 teaspoon truffle salt (if you don't have truffle salt, it's okay, just use regular)
2 tablespoons melted butter (you could use shmaltz, if you are not vegetarian)
4 small carrots or 2 large, roughly chopped
2 quarts Imagine "No Chicken" broth or homemade vegetable stock

recipe.label: Vegetarian Ramen
ingredientLines: 1 onion, cut in half (you can leave the skin on)
2 stalks lemongrass, cut into thirds and smashed (optional)
1 sheet kombu, wiped with a damp cloth
2 tablespoons bonito flakes (technically not vegetarian, but recommended for fish eaters)
1 to 2 squirts sriracha, or pinch of red pepper flakes
1 packet extra-firm tofu, pressed of its moisture
1 tablespoon oil with high smoke point, like peanut
4 packets ramen or udon noodles, preferably fresh

recipe.label: Vegetarian Minestrone
ingredientLines: 3 stalks celery, small dice (reserve leaves for garnish)
2 cups small diced waxy potatoes, skin on
1 handful green beans, ends trimmed, cut in 1/2" lengths
3 cups finely shredded cabbage (savoy or green)

1-2 tablespoons vegetable broth powder; i like seitenbacher (double check gluten free/vegan status if important to you). don't be tempted to use a thick vegetarian broth; you can use a pre-mixed one as long as it is a clear brown type that tastes good.
1 15 oz. can good quality whole italian tomatoes with juice
1 15 oz. can cannelini or white navy beans, drained and rinsed

recipe.label: Quorn Chilli (Vegetarian)
ingredientLines: 1 and a half tbsp Olive oil
2 x 350g (2 x 12oz) packets of quorn mince
2 x 400g (2 x 14oz) tins red kidney beans in chilli sauce
2 peppers, diced (ideally two different colours e.g 1 red and 1 green)
2 tsp mild chili powder (you can add more later)
1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce or vegetarian equivalent
End of a teaspoon of chinese five spice
